omments by Roger de Piles).</li>\n<li><i>Dialogue sur le coloris</i> ( <i>Dialogue upon Colour</i>, 1673)</li>\n<li><i>Le Cabinet de Monseigneur le Duc de <a href=\"/wiki/Cardinal_Richelieu\" title=\"Cardinal Richelieu\">Richelieu</a></i> (1676)</li>\n<li><i>Lettre d'un fran\u00e7ais \u00e0 un gentilhomme flamand</i> (1676)</li>\n<li><i>La Vie de Rubens</i> (1681)</li>\n<li><i>L'Abr\u00e9g\u00e9 de la vie des peintres</i> (1699),<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> a seven-volume book of painter biographies:\n<ul><li>The list of painters in Part 5: <a href=\"/wiki/Roger_de_Piles%27_artists_from_Lombardy\" title=\"Roger de Piles&#39; artists from Lombardy\">Roger de Piles' artists from Lombardy</a></li>\n<li>The list of painters in Part 6: <a href=\"/wiki/Roger_de_Piles%27_artists_from_Germany_and_the_Low_Countries\" title=\"Roger de Piles&#39; artists from Germany and the Low Countries\">Roger de Piles' artists from Germany and the Low Countries</a></li>\n<li>The list of painters in Part 7: <a href=\"/wiki/Roger_de_Piles%27_artists_from_France\" title=\"Roger de Piles&#39; artists from France\">Roger de Piles' artists from France</a></li></ul></li>\n<li><i>Cours de peinture par principes avec un balance de peintres</i> ( <i>The Principles of Painting</i>, 1708), see: <a href=\"/wiki/Formal_analysis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Formal analysis\">formal analysis</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Roger_de_Piles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"Epitome of the life of the painters... with a treaty on the perfect painter\".</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=i9RPAQAAIAAJ\">English translation in 1707</a> <i>The Art of Painting and the Lives of the Painters</i> on <a href=\"/wiki/Google_books\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Google books\">Google books</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Roger_de_Piles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Skliar-Piguet, Alexandra (1996). \"Roger de Piles\".  In Jane Turner. <i>The Dictionary of Art</i>. London, New York: Grove-Macmillan Publishers.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Roger+de+Piles&amp;rft.btitle=The+Dictionary+of+Art&amp;rft.place=London%2C+New+York&amp;rft.pub=Grove-Macmillan+Publishers&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.aulast=Skliar-Piguet&amp;rft.aufirst=Alexandra&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARoger+de+Piles\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Teyss\u00e8dre, Bernard (1957). <i>Roger de Piles et les d\u00e9bats sur le coloris au si\u00e8cle de Louis XIV</i>. Paris: Biblioth\u00e8que des Arts.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Roger+de+Piles+et+les+d%C3%A9bats+sur+le+coloris+au+si%C3%A8cle+de+Louis+XIV&amp;rft.place=Paris&amp;rft.pub=Biblioth%C3%A8que+des+Arts&amp;rft.date=1957&am